Title: Good Eats: The Complete Second Season

reviewText: Okay, first - really do love all the episodes of Good Eats I have watched. That said - Food Network, please release these videos by season! Why? I am glad you asked! Alton Brown wrote 3 large books with tons and tons of information (Volume 1 the Early Years, Volume 2 the Middle Years, Volume 3 the Later Years). Each book is written by, you guessed it - episode! The books are packed with information and make a great middle school/high school food science curriculum/culinary (backed up with additional sources yes) program.Of course, you need the episodes to go along with each chapter of the book. By not having the seasons released - the value of what this book could actually "do" is diminished quite a bit. So, could you maybe do the world a favor (okay, maybe not the entire world, how about food nerds with little food nerds) a let these two same named projects be used in tandem with each other as intended.
Title: Good Eats: The Complete Second Season

reviewText: Alton Brown is one of my favorite TV chefs. Less for the specific recipes than for his approach to food and teaching cooking as opposed to just following a plan he teaches people to actually cook all covering it in a mass of pop culture references.In the past the Food channel has released his programs in topic focused sets- holiday foods/roasts/ fish etc. but for the real fan the whole season is more fun as you can rediscover episodes maybe you missed and wouldn’t get in the topic.That having been said the price of these, as good as they are, at $100 is way too high. I’d suggest looking elsewhere and hoping that the Food TV people release later season on DVD.
summary: a great cooking show that really teaches to cook.
Title: Good Eats: The Complete Second Season

Title: Good Eats: The Complete Second Season

reviewText: Good Eats was at it's best earlier in the franchise, so this is another great season.  Alton Brown is witty, smart and just plain fun to watch.Target sold seasons 1 and 2 - I'm doubtful we will get the rest of the seasons in the proper complete season format, but well worth your purchase for a great TV show.
